{"id":"quiz8","titre":"Grammar: Expressing Purpose","questions":[{"id":"q1","type":"qcm","enonce":"How do you express purpose (the 'why') in English ?","options":["To + base verb","For + base verb","Because + base verb","So + base verb"],"correctIndex":0},{"id":"q2","type":"vrai_faux","enonce":"'So that' is followed by a clause (subject + modal verb like can/will).","reponse":true},{"id":"q3","type":"trous","enonce":"Complete: The artist used a stencil {{1}} (in order) to work faster.","reponsesAttendues":["in order / so as"]},{"id":"q4","type":"relier","question":"Match.","pairs":[{"left":"He paints to...","right":"...express his feelings."},{"left":"He paints so that...","right":"...people can see his vision."},{"left":"He paints for...","right":"...pleasure."}]},{"id":"q5","type":"qcm","enonce":"Which form is incorrect for expressing purpose ?","options":["To express","So that people see","For express","In order to express"],"correctIndex":2}]}